60/* isInlineItem indicates whether the object needs to be passed through IPC::Encoder in order to serialize,
61 * or whether we can just use placement new and be done.
62 * It needs to match (1) RemoteImageBufferProxy::encodeItem(), (2) RemoteRenderingBackend::decodeItem(),
63 * and (3) isInlineItem() in DisplayListItemType.cpp.
64 *
65 * isDrawingItem indicates if this command can affect dirty rects.
66 * We can do things like skip drawing items when replaying them if their extents don't intersect with the current clip.
67 * It needs to match isDrawingItem() in DisplayListItemType.cpp. */
68

268class SetState {
269public:
270 static constexpr ItemType itemType = ItemType::SetState;
271 static constexpr bool isInlineItem = false;
272 static constexpr bool isDrawingItem = false;
273
274 WEBCORE_EXPORT SetState(const GraphicsContextState&, GraphicsContextState::StateChangeFlags);
275
276 const GraphicsContextStateChange& stateChange() const { return m_stateChange; }
277 const Pattern::Parameters& strokePatternParameters() const { return m_strokePattern.parameters; }
278 const Pattern::Parameters& fillPatternParameters() const { return m_fillPattern.parameters; }
279 RenderingResourceIdentifier strokePatternImageIdentifier() const { return m_strokePattern.tileImageIdentifier; }
280 RenderingResourceIdentifier fillPatternImageIdentifier() const { return m_fillPattern.tileImageIdentifier; }
281
282 template<class Encoder> void encode(Encoder&) const;
283 template<class Decoder> static std::optional<SetState> decode(Decoder&);
284
285 void apply(GraphicsContext&, NativeImage* strokePatternImage, NativeImage* fillPatternImage);
286
287private:
288 struct PatternData {
289 RenderingResourceIdentifier tileImageIdentifier;
290 Pattern::Parameters parameters;
291 };
292
293 WEBCORE_EXPORT SetState(const GraphicsContextStateChange&, const PatternData& strokePattern, const PatternData& fillPattern);
294
295 GraphicsContextStateChange m_stateChange;
296 PatternData m_strokePattern;
297 PatternData m_fillPattern;
298};

300template<class Encoder>
301void SetState::encode(Encoder& encoder) const
302{
303 auto changeFlags = m_stateChange.m_changeFlags;
304 encoder << changeFlags;
305
306 auto& state = m_stateChange.m_state;
307
308 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokeGradientChange)) {
309 ASSERT(state.strokeGradient);
310 encoder << *state.strokeGradient;
311 }
312
313 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokePatternChange)) {
314 ASSERT(state.strokePattern);
315 encoder << state.strokePattern->tileImage().renderingResourceIdentifier();
316 encoder << state.strokePattern->parameters();
317 }
318
319 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::FillGradientChange)) {
320 ASSERT(state.fillGradient);
321 encoder << *state.fillGradient;
322 }
323
324 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::FillPatternChange)) {
325 ASSERT(state.fillPattern);
326 encoder << state.fillPattern->tileImage().renderingResourceIdentifier();
327 encoder << state.fillPattern->parameters();
328 }
329
330 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShadowChange)) {
331 encoder << state.shadowOffset;
332 encoder << state.shadowBlur;
333 encoder << state.shadowColor;
334 encoder << state.shadowRadiusMode;
335 }
336
337 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokeThicknessChange))
338 encoder << state.strokeThickness;
339
340 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::TextDrawingModeChange))
341 encoder << state.textDrawingMode;
342
343 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokeColorChange))
344 encoder << state.strokeColor;
345
346 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::FillColorChange))
347 encoder << state.fillColor;
348
349 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokeStyleChange))
350 encoder << state.strokeStyle;
351
352 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::FillRuleChange))
353 encoder << state.fillRule;
354
355 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::CompositeOperationChange))
356 encoder << state.compositeOperator;
357
358 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::BlendModeChange))
359 encoder << state.blendMode;
360
361 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ImageInterpolationQualityChange))
362 encoder << state.imageInterpolationQuality;
363
364 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::AlphaChange))
365 encoder << state.alpha;
366
367 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShouldAntialiasChange))
368 encoder << state.shouldAntialias;
369
370 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShouldSmoothFontsChange))
371 encoder << state.shouldSmoothFonts;
372
373 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShouldSubpixelQuantizeFontsChange))
374 encoder << state.shouldSubpixelQuantizeFonts;
375
376 if (changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShadowsIgnoreTransformsChange))
377 encoder << state.shadowsIgnoreTransforms;
378}
379
380template<class Decoder>
381std::optional<SetState> SetState::decode(Decoder& decoder)
382{
383 std::optional<GraphicsContextState::StateChangeFlags> changeFlags;
384 decoder >> changeFlags;
385 if (!changeFlags)
386 return std::nullopt;
387
388 GraphicsContextStateChange stateChange;
389 stateChange.m_changeFlags = *changeFlags;
390
391 PatternData strokePattern;
392 PatternData fillPattern;
393
394 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokeGradientChange)) {
395 auto strokeGradient = Gradient::decode(decoder);
396 if (!strokeGradient)
397 return std::nullopt;
398
399 stateChange.m_state.strokeGradient = WTFMove(*strokeGradient);
400 }
401
402 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokePatternChange)) {
403 std::optional<RenderingResourceIdentifier> renderingResourceIdentifier;
404 decoder >> renderingResourceIdentifier;
405 if (!renderingResourceIdentifier)
406 return std::nullopt;
407
408 std::optional<Pattern::Parameters> parameters;
409 decoder >> parameters;
410 if (!parameters)
411 return std::nullopt;
412
413 strokePattern = { *renderingResourceIdentifier, *parameters };
414 }
415
416 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::FillGradientChange)) {
417 auto fillGradient = Gradient::decode(decoder);
418 if (!fillGradient)
419 return std::nullopt;
420
421 stateChange.m_state.fillGradient = WTFMove(*fillGradient);
422 }
423
424 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::FillPatternChange)) {
425 std::optional<RenderingResourceIdentifier> renderingResourceIdentifier;
426 decoder >> renderingResourceIdentifier;
427 if (!renderingResourceIdentifier)
428 return std::nullopt;
429
430 std::optional<Pattern::Parameters> parameters;
431 decoder >> parameters;
432 if (!parameters)
433 return std::nullopt;
434
435 fillPattern = { *renderingResourceIdentifier, *parameters };
436 }
437
438 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShadowChange)) {
439 std::optional<FloatSize> shadowOffset;
440 decoder >> shadowOffset;
441 if (!shadowOffset)
442 return std::nullopt;
443
444 stateChange.m_state.shadowOffset = *shadowOffset;
445
446 std::optional<float> shadowBlur;
447 decoder >> shadowBlur;
448 if (!shadowBlur)
449 return std::nullopt;
450
451 stateChange.m_state.shadowBlur = *shadowBlur;
452
453 std::optional<Color> shadowColor;
454 decoder >> shadowColor;
455 if (!shadowColor)
456 return std::nullopt;
457
458 stateChange.m_state.shadowColor = *shadowColor;
459
460 std::optional<ShadowRadiusMode> shadowRadiusMode;
461 decoder >> shadowRadiusMode;
462 if (!shadowRadiusMode)
463 return std::nullopt;
464
465 stateChange.m_state.shadowRadiusMode = WTFMove(*shadowRadiusMode);
466 }
467
468 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokeThicknessChange)) {
469 std::optional<float> strokeThickness;
470 decoder >> strokeThickness;
471 if (!strokeThickness)
472 return std::nullopt;
473
474 stateChange.m_state.strokeThickness = *strokeThickness;
475 }
476
477 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::TextDrawingModeChange)) {
478 std::optional<TextDrawingModeFlags> textDrawingMode;
479 decoder >> textDrawingMode;
480 if (!textDrawingMode)
481 return std::nullopt;
482
483 stateChange.m_state.textDrawingMode = WTFMove(*textDrawingMode);
484 }
485
486 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokeColorChange)) {
487 std::optional<Color> strokeColor;
488 decoder >> strokeColor;
489 if (!strokeColor)
490 return std::nullopt;
491
492 stateChange.m_state.strokeColor = *strokeColor;
493 }
494
495 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::FillColorChange)) {
496 std::optional<Color> fillColor;
497 decoder >> fillColor;
498 if (!fillColor)
499 return std::nullopt;
500
501 stateChange.m_state.fillColor = *fillColor;
502 }
503
504 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::StrokeStyleChange)) {
505 StrokeStyle strokeStyle;
506 if (!decoder.decode(strokeStyle))
507 return std::nullopt;
508
509 stateChange.m_state.strokeStyle = strokeStyle;
510 }
511
512 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::FillRuleChange)) {
513 std::optional<WindRule> fillRule;
514 decoder >> fillRule;
515 if (!fillRule)
516 return std::nullopt;
517
518 stateChange.m_state.fillRule = *fillRule;
519 }
520
521 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::CompositeOperationChange)) {
522 std::optional<CompositeOperator> compositeOperator;
523 decoder >> compositeOperator;
524 if (!compositeOperator)
525 return std::nullopt;
526
527 stateChange.m_state.compositeOperator = *compositeOperator;
528 }
529
530 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::BlendModeChange)) {
531 std::optional<BlendMode> blendMode;
532 decoder >> blendMode;
533 if (!blendMode)
534 return std::nullopt;
535
536 stateChange.m_state.blendMode = *blendMode;
537 }
538
539 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ImageInterpolationQualityChange)) {
540 std::optional<InterpolationQuality> imageInterpolationQuality;
541 decoder >> imageInterpolationQuality;
542 if (!imageInterpolationQuality)
543 return std::nullopt;
544
545 stateChange.m_state.imageInterpolationQuality = *imageInterpolationQuality;
546 }
547
548 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::AlphaChange)) {
549 std::optional<float> alpha;
550 decoder >> alpha;
551 if (!alpha)
552 return std::nullopt;
553
554 stateChange.m_state.alpha = *alpha;
555 }
556
557 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShouldAntialiasChange)) {
558 std::optional<bool> shouldAntialias;
559 decoder >> shouldAntialias;
560 if (!shouldAntialias)
561 return std::nullopt;
562
563 stateChange.m_state.shouldAntialias = *shouldAntialias;
564 }
565
566 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShouldSmoothFontsChange)) {
567 std::optional<bool> shouldSmoothFonts;
568 decoder >> shouldSmoothFonts;
569 if (!shouldSmoothFonts)
570 return std::nullopt;
571
572 stateChange.m_state.shouldSmoothFonts = *shouldSmoothFonts;
573 }
574
575 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShouldSubpixelQuantizeFontsChange)) {
576 std::optional<bool> shouldSubpixelQuantizeFonts;
577 decoder >> shouldSubpixelQuantizeFonts;
578 if (!shouldSubpixelQuantizeFonts)
579 return std::nullopt;
580
581 stateChange.m_state.shouldSubpixelQuantizeFonts = *shouldSubpixelQuantizeFonts;
582 }
583
584 if (stateChange.m_changeFlags.contains(GraphicsContextState::ShadowsIgnoreTransformsChange)) {
585 std::optional<bool> shadowsIgnoreTransforms;
586 decoder >> shadowsIgnoreTransforms;
587 if (!shadowsIgnoreTransforms)
588 return std::nullopt;
589
590 stateChange.m_state.shadowsIgnoreTransforms = *shadowsIgnoreTransforms;
591 }
592
593 return {{ stateChange, strokePattern, fillPattern }};
594}

654

656 decoder >> dashOffset;
657 if (!dashOffset)
658 return std::nullopt;
659
660 return {{ *dashArray, *dashOffset }};
661}

954 DrawGlyphs(const Font&, const GlyphBufferGlyph*, const GlyphBufferAdvance*, unsigned count, const FloatPoint& localAnchor, FontSmoothingMode);
955 WEBCORE_EXPORT DrawGlyphs(RenderingResourceIdentifier, Vector<GlyphBufferGlyph, 128>&&, Vector<GlyphBufferAdvance, 128>&&, const FloatRect&, const FloatPoint& localAnchor, FontSmoothingMode);

972
973template<class Encoder>
974void DrawGlyphs::encode(Encoder& encoder) const
975{
976 encoder << m_fontIdentifier;
977 encoder << m_glyphs;
978 encoder << m_advances;
979 encoder << m_bounds;
980 encoder << m_localAnchor;
981 encoder << m_smoothingMode;
982}
983
984template<class Decoder>
985std::optional<DrawGlyphs> DrawGlyphs::decode(Decoder& decoder)
986{
987 std::optional<RenderingResourceIdentifier> fontIdentifier;
988 decoder >> fontIdentifier;
989 if (!fontIdentifier)
990 return std::nullopt;
991
992 std::optional<Vector<GlyphBufferGlyph, 128>> glyphs;
993 decoder >> glyphs;
994 if (!glyphs)
995 return std::nullopt;
996
997 std::optional<Vector<GlyphBufferAdvance, 128>> advances;
998 decoder >> advances;
999 if (!advances)
1000 return std::nullopt;
1001
1002 if (glyphs->size() != advances->size())
1003 return std::nullopt;
1004
1005 std::optional<FloatRect> bounds;
1006 decoder >> bounds;
1007 if (!bounds)
1008 return std::nullopt;
1009
1010 std::optional<FloatPoint> localAnchor;
1011 decoder >> localAnchor;
1012 if (!localAnchor)
1013 return std::nullopt;
1014
1015 std::optional<FontSmoothingMode> smoothingMode;
1016 decoder >> smoothingMode;
1017 if (!smoothingMode)
1018 return std::nullopt;
1019
1020 return {{ *fontIdentifier, WTFMove(*glyphs), WTFMove(*advances), *bounds, *localAnchor, *smoothingMode }};
1021}
